HEADWORD: Aquosity
<hw>A*quos"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>aquositas</ets>.]</ety> <def>The condition of being wet or watery;
wateriness.</def> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Very little water or <qex>aquosity</qex> is found in their
belly.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

